For Initialization of Git : git init

For Commiting Changes into Branch with a Comment : git commit -m "This is Commit Format"

For Checking The Changes Wrked or Not : git status

To Add The Entire Files of a Folder : git add .
To Add The Particular File of a Folder : git add <file_path>

To Add The remote branch to The Main Brain : git remote add origin <gitHub repo Link>  
ex:git remote add origin https://github.com/NV-Manoj/myPortfolio.git

To Push The Changes Made in Master to The Origin/Main branch : git push origin master

<!-- //////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////// -->

Basic Git Commands:

For Initialization of Git ---> git init

For Committing Changes into Branch with a Comment ---> git commit -m "This is Commit Format"

For Checking The Changes Worked or Not ---> git status

To Add The Entire Files of a Folder ---> git add .

To Add The Particular File of a Folder ---> git add <file_path>

To Add The Remote Branch to The Main Brain ---> git remote add origin

To Push The Changes Made in Master to The Origin/Main Branch ---> git push origin master

Additional Git Commands:

To Clone a Repository ---> git clone <repository_url>

To Create a New Branch ---> git branch <branch_name>

To Switch to a Different Branch ---> git checkout <branch_name>

To Create and Switch to a New Branch ---> git checkout -b <branch_name>

To Merge Branches ---> git merge <branch_name>

To View Commit History ---> git log

To Stash Changes (Temporarily Save Work) ---> git stash

To Apply Stashed Changes ---> git stash pop

To Pull Latest Changes from Remote ---> git pull origin master
